Subject: [PATCH 2/2] COMP: Add VTK::CommonCore dependency to Units Logic

VTK 9.x has empty VTK_INCLUDE_DIRS; headers only propagate through CMake
IMPORTED targets.  The Logic library had an empty TARGET_LIBRARIES list so
nothing brought vtkObject.h into the include path.  Adding VTK::CommonCore
fixes the missing vtkObject.h error in standalone builds.
---
 Modules/Loadable/Units/Logic/CMakeLists.txt | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/Modules/Loadable/Units/Logic/CMakeLists.txt b/Modules/Loadable/Units/Logic/CMakeLists.txt
index 46e6e415af..2ddcd76f0b 100644
--- a/Modules/Loadable/Units/Logic/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/Modules/Loadable/Units/Logic/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -33,6 +33,7 @@ set(${KIT}_SRCS
   )
 
 set(${KIT}_TARGET_LIBRARIES
+  VTK::CommonCore
   )
 
